
[1]perilous

   PER'ILOUS, a. Dangerous; hazardous; full of risk; as a perilous
   undertaking; a perilous situation.

   1. Vulgarly used for very, like mighty; as perilous shrewd.

   2. Smart; witty; as a perilous [parlous boy.]

   [Vulgar and obsolete.]
